    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice the<strong> red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add<strong> </strong>3/4<strong> </strong>of the <strong>diced red\u00a0onion</strong>\u00a0(you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then cook for 5 min or until softened and starting to caramelise</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-pork-chilli-with-apple-salsa/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>diced\u00a0red onion</strong> to a medium-sized bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and the <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and set aside to pickle \u2013 this is your <strong>quick-pickled red onion</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-pork-chilli-with-apple-salsa/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Stir the <strong>ground allspice</strong> into the softened\u00a0onion and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>pork mince</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-pork-chilli-with-apple-salsa/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> bulgur wheat</strong>\u00a0to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook over a high heat for 7-9 min or until tender with a slight bite, then drain and return to the pot</p><p>While the bulgur wheat is cooking, dissolve the<strong> beef\u00a0stock mix</strong>\u00a0in 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-pork-chilli-with-apple-salsa/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mince has browned, stir in the <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>beef\u00a0stock</strong> and reduce the heat to medium-low</p><p>Cook for 10-15 min or until thick and reduced to a chilli-like consistency \u2013 this is your<strong>\u00a0Mexican-style pork chilli</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-pork-chilli-with-apple-salsa/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chilli thickens, finely dice the <strong>apple<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>(skin on)</p><p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-pork-chilli-with-apple-salsa/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> diced apple</strong> to the<strong> quick-pickled red onion</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and season lightly with <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong>\u00a0\u2013 this is your <strong>apple salsa</strong></p><p>Fluff the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>bulgur</strong> with a fork</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-pork-chilli-with-apple-salsa/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Mexican-style pork chilli</strong> over the <strong>fluffed\u00a0bulgur\u00a0</strong>with the <strong>apple salsa</strong> to the side</p><p>Top with the <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
